metadata.name: The Commute
metadata.description:
Location // Manchester, U.K.
Date // June 21st, 2022
Camera // Canon 5D Mark 1v
Exposure // 1/200
F-stop // f/7

Some would say the commute is mundane but I feel differently about this underrated ritual.

I’ve always been fascinated by the electric energy that buzzes around the city in the morning as people rush to their 9 to 5. 
I find comfort and purpose in the repetition. Watching the world wake up is one of life’s true gifts.

The commute is about time, time to relax, time to think, time to plan and time to understand.
